WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.834 --> 00:00:03.636
"Get to the microwave...

00:00:03.669 --> 00:00:06.039
...in as few steps
as possible.

00:00:06.072 --> 00:00:09.976
Open the door before
the microwave dings.

00:00:10.009 --> 00:00:11.544
Fewest steps wins.

00:00:11.577 --> 00:00:13.513
There are 5 minutes
on the clock.

00:00:13.546 --> 00:00:15.515
The microwave starts now."

00:00:15.548 --> 00:00:16.582
Where's the microwave?

00:00:16.615 --> 00:00:18.518
[ Humming ]

00:00:18.551 --> 00:00:20.653
Where's the micr-- Inside?

00:00:20.686 --> 00:00:21.988
Have you seen
the microwave?

00:00:22.021 --> 00:00:23.056
No.

00:00:23.089 --> 00:00:24.524
-In the shed?
-Yeah.

00:00:24.557 --> 00:00:26.259
Fewest steps?!

00:00:26.292 --> 00:00:27.093
Damn it!

00:00:27.126 --> 00:00:29.862
[ Cheering and applause ]

00:00:29.895 --> 00:00:32.498
I structured the wording
in such a way that

00:00:32.531 --> 00:00:34.667
there would be no possibility

00:00:34.700 --> 00:00:37.403
of people just, you know,
taking steps.

00:00:37.436 --> 00:00:38.604
No, and these are
clever people as well.

00:00:38.637 --> 00:00:39.772
No one's just gonna
take big steps.

00:00:39.805 --> 00:00:40.873
-[Laughing]
-No.

00:00:40.906 --> 00:00:42.275
-Do you wanna see Dillon?
-Yes.

00:00:42.308 --> 00:00:42.875
-Okay.
[ Laughter ]

00:00:42.908 --> 00:00:44.677
Ahhhhh!

00:00:44.710 --> 00:00:46.012
♪♪

00:00:46.045 --> 00:00:48.448
2, [laughing] 3,
[ Laughter ]

00:00:48.481 --> 00:00:50.483
4, 5.

00:00:50.516 --> 00:00:52.819
♪♪

00:00:52.852 --> 00:00:56.022
[ Laughter ]
Maybe hopping's better?

00:00:56.055 --> 00:00:58.224
♪♪

00:00:58.257 --> 00:01:05.098
Uhh! 19, 20, 21, 22, 23.

00:01:05.131 --> 00:01:08.935
26, 27, 28, 29.

00:01:08.968 --> 00:01:10.770
[ Humming ]

00:01:10.803 --> 00:01:13.473
[ Ding! ]

00:01:13.506 --> 00:01:14.740
A potato.

00:01:14.773 --> 00:01:16.008
Is that it?

00:01:16.041 --> 00:01:17.577
Yeah, I mean, you got
here very quickly.

00:01:17.610 --> 00:01:20.012
You thought about it
for...8 seconds,

00:01:20.045 --> 00:01:21.347
which is longer
than usual.

00:01:21.380 --> 00:01:22.915
[ Laughter ]

00:01:22.948 --> 00:01:24.317
You're a dick.

00:01:24.350 --> 00:01:26.652
[ Cheering and applause ]

00:01:26.685 --> 00:01:28.154
You went with the big steps.

00:01:28.187 --> 00:01:31.057
I have long legs, so,
why not use them?

00:01:31.090 --> 00:01:32.325
You got there in 30 seconds

00:01:32.358 --> 00:01:34.227
and you only took 29 steps,
so, I mean,

00:01:34.260 --> 00:01:35.428
it's the lowest, so far.

00:01:35.461 --> 00:01:36.896
-So far.
-Yeah.

00:01:36.929 --> 00:01:38.164
[ Laughter ]

00:01:38.197 --> 00:01:39.398
We're gonna see
if somebody can come up

00:01:39.431 --> 00:01:40.600
with a different way.

00:01:40.633 --> 00:01:42.435
Shall we look at...
[ Laughter ]

00:01:42.468 --> 00:01:44.937
Ron and Freddie?

00:01:44.970 --> 00:01:47.640
Fewest steps wins.

00:01:47.673 --> 00:01:49.175
Is this a step?

00:01:49.208 --> 00:01:50.610
That's not really
a step, is it?

00:01:50.643 --> 00:01:51.978
That's just crawling.

00:01:52.011 --> 00:01:53.079
I'm gonna crawl it.

00:01:53.112 --> 00:01:54.547
This doesn't count
as steps, right?

00:01:54.580 --> 00:01:55.882
If you say so.

00:01:55.915 --> 00:01:57.750
I feel like there are no steps
involved in this!

00:01:57.783 --> 00:01:59.185
[ Laughter ]

00:01:59.218 --> 00:02:01.220
[ Continues indistinctly ]

00:02:01.253 --> 00:02:04.123
♪♪

00:02:04.156 --> 00:02:06.159
Ron:
Not great for the knees,
I'll tell you that.

00:02:06.192 --> 00:02:08.361
[ Laughter ]

00:02:08.394 --> 00:02:11.330
♪♪

00:02:11.363 --> 00:02:14.901
That is not good,
but I gotta win.

00:02:14.934 --> 00:02:18.504
♪♪

00:02:18.537 --> 00:02:20.173
Audience: Ohhhhh!

00:02:20.206 --> 00:02:21.007
Okay, that's worse.

00:02:21.040 --> 00:02:22.341
[ Laughter ]

00:02:22.374 --> 00:02:24.644
-You think you made it?
-I think, hopefully.

00:02:24.677 --> 00:02:25.845
-Hi, Ron.
-Hi!

00:02:25.878 --> 00:02:27.847
-How's your day going?
-So far, so good.

00:02:27.880 --> 00:02:30.116
[ Humming ]
-[ Gasp ]

00:02:30.149 --> 00:02:31.817
That's for me,
I'm afraid.

00:02:31.850 --> 00:02:32.919
Just in time.

00:02:32.952 --> 00:02:35.021
Hey!

00:02:35.054 --> 00:02:35.721
Thanks, Ron.

00:02:35.754 --> 00:02:36.622
Thank you!

00:02:36.655 --> 00:02:38.591
Audience: Awww!

00:02:38.624 --> 00:02:40.957
-That's quite hot, isn't it?
-Whahh!

